title: MiniMax body shape on error log line is enormous and crowds out other errors
---
## Summary

When MiniMax returns HTTP 400 (e.g. error 2013 'tool call result does not
follow tool call' before B620 was fixed, or B634's empty-args feedback
loop), `src/provider_minimax.ml` calls
`Provider.summarize_anthropic_messages` which emits a single WARN line of
many hundreds of bytes:

  WARN MiniMax body shape on error (HTTP 400): A[txt] A[1tu] U[1tr]
  A[1tu] U[1tr] A[1tu] U[1tr] U[txt] A[4tu] U[4tr] A[1tu] U[1tr] U[txt]
  A[2tu] U[2tr] ... [continues for ~150+ A/U tokens]

3+ occurrences in current daemon.log, each ~2 KB.

Purpose is fine (diagnose history shape) but the line dominates the
visible log around the actual error.

## Suggested fix

1. Wrap the summary in a multi-line breakdown or truncate to last N=20
   blocks.
2. Or: gate behind a `MINIMAX_DEBUG_BODY` env var so it only fires when
   actively debugging.
3. Or: emit at DEBUG severity by default, INFO only when MINIMAX_DEBUG_BODY
   is set.

## Evidence

- src/provider_minimax.ml line 198-200 (non-stream) and 263-265 (stream)
- ~/.clawq/daemon.log: search 'MiniMax body shape on error'